==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nine-bark
<hw>Nine"-bark`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A white-flowered rosaceous shrub (<spn>Neillia opulifolia</spn>, or
<spn>Spiraea opulifolia</spn>), common in the Northern United States.
The bark separates into many thin layers, whence the name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nine-eyes</ent>⟦br⟧
